low is a summary of all 12 points in the final:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! N. !! Contestant !! Voting nation\n|-\n| 9 || '''[[Estonia in the Eurovision Song Contest 2001|Estonia]]''' || Greece, Latvia, Lithuania, Malta, Netherlands, Poland, Slovenia, Turkey, United Kingdom\n|-\n| 6 || [[Denmark in the Eurovision Song Contest 2001|Denmark]] || Iceland, Croatia, Estonia, Germany, Ireland, Norway\n|-\n| 3 || [[France in the Eurovision Song Contest 2001|France]] || Bosnia and Herzegovina, Portugal, Russia   \n|-\n| 2 || [[Greece in the Eurovision Song Contest 2001|Greece]]  || Spain, Sweden\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"| 1\n| [[Spain in the Eurovision Song Contest 2001|Spain]] || Israel\n|-\n| [[Malta in the Eurovision Song Contest 2001|Malta]]  || Denmark\n|-\n| [[Portugal in the Eurovision Song Contest 2001|Portugal]]  || France\n|}\n\n== International broadcasts and voting ==\n===Voting and spokespersons===\nThe spokespersons announced the score from their respective country's televote (or, in some cases, national jury) in running order.\n{{Div col}}\n#{{Esc|Netherlands}} \u2013 [[Marlayne]] <small>(Dutch representative in {{Escyr|1999}})</small>\n#{{Esc|Iceland}} \u2013 Eva Mar\u00eda J\u00f3nsd\u00f3ttir \n#{{Esc|Bosnia and Herzegovina}} \u2013 Segmedina Srna\n#{{Esc|Norway}} \u2013 [[Roald \u00d8yen]]\n#{{Esc|Israel}} \u2013 Yoav Ginai<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sf.tapuz.co.il/shirshur-262-1949782.htm |title=\u05e4\u05d5\u05e8\u05d5\u05dd \u05d0\u05d9\u05e8\u05d5\u05d5\u05d9\u05d6\u05d9\u05d5\u05df |publisher=Sf.tapuz.co.il |date=1999-09-13 |accessdate=2012-08-09 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111008025322/http://sf.tapuz.co.il/shirshur-262-1949782.htm |archivedate=8 October 2011 }}</ref>\n#{{Esc|Russia}} \u2013 Larisa Verbitskaya\n#{{Esc|Sweden}} \u2013 [[Josefine Sundstr\u00f6m]]<ref name=\"infosajten.com\"/>\n#{{Esc|Lithuania|1988}} \u2013 Loreta Tarozait\u0117<ref>{{cite web|author=BNS |url=http://pramogos.delfi.lt/