 You (Antique song)|Die for You]]\n| length22 = 2:56\n| note23 = {{Esccnty|Denmark}}\n| extra23 = [[Rollo & King]] \n| title23 = [[Never Ever Let You Go]]\n| length23 = 3:00\n}}\n\n=== Charts ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2001)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br /> position\n|-\n{{albumchart|GermanyComp|4|M|title=Eurovision Song Contest 2001|url=https://www.offiziellecharts.de/compilation-details-14495|work=Offiziellecharts.de|publisher=[[GfK Entertainment Charts]]|rowheader=true|accessdate=17 March 2018}}\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{Official website|http://www.eurovision.tv/}}\n\n{{Eurovision years}}\n{{Eurovision Song Contest 2001}}\n{{Eurovision Song Contest's Greatest Hits}}\n{{Aqua (band)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2012}}\n{{coord|55|42|08.89|N|12|34|19.93|E|type:landmark_region:DK_scale:2000|display=title}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Eurovision Song Contest by year]]\n[[Category:2001 music festivals]]\n[[Category:2001 in Denmark]]\n[[Category:Eurovision Song Contest 2001| ]]\n[[Category:2000s in Copenhagen]]\n[[Category:Culture in Copenhagen]]\n[[Category:May 2001 events in Europe]]\n[[Category:Events in Copenhagen]]\n", "name_user": "WEBDuB", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eurovision_Song_Contest_2001"}
